### OCR: Image to Text Converter
This project demonstrates how to bridge the gap between physical images and digital text. 
Using OpenCV for image processing and Pytesseract for Optical Character Recognition (OCR), 
I built a tool that reads text from an image and exports it into a clean, editable text file.

## Key Skills:

-Image preprocessing (converting to grayscale).
-Integrating the Tesseract engine for text extraction.
-Saving processed data to external files.

## Technologies Used

- Python
- OpenCV
- Pytesseract
- Matplotlib
